No tortillas left? Or ate too many tortillas? 😂 LETTUCE WRAP with cilantro lime rice, mashed black beans, and chipotle carrots 🥕I found this massive carrot at my local market so I made a similar recipe to my carrot ti ha (on my ebook). In a pan I sautéed white onions and carrots until soft (with a soft crunch). Then I added a red sauce (blend 1 can of chipotle in adobo sauce with 1-2 Roma tomatoes). Using parchment paper roll your lettuce leaves 🥬 making a big burrito 🌯 #throwback 

Neto Craves 💚 
➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖
Te quedaste sin tortillas? O comiste demasiadas tortillas? 😂 ENVOLTURA DE LECHUGA con arroz (cilantro/lime), puré de frijoles negros y zanahorias con chipotle🥕Encontré esta zanahoria enorme en mi mercado local, así que hice una receta similar a la de mi tinga (está en mi ebook). En un sartén dora cebollas y zanahorias hasta que estén blandas (con un crujido suave). Luego agregué una salsa roja (licue 1 lata de chipotle en salsa de adobo con 1-2 tomates Roma). Usando papel pergamino enrolle las hojas de lechuga 🥬 haciendo un burrito grande🌯. ¿Qué le pondrías al tuyo? Para mí, la mezcla de zanahoria fue lo que le dio sabor. 😋

Spicy Potatoes 🔥 
For this recipe, I will be using Choose-a-Crock Programmable Slow Cooker from @crockpot

Ingredients:
10-15 small golden potatoes 
1-2 cups of tomato sauce 
1 cup of veggie broth 
1/2 white onion 
1 tbsp smoked paprika 
2 garlic cloves 
5-8 chiles de Arbol
Salt to taste 
1 tbsp Chili garlic sauce (optional) 
In a pan, add your diced onions, minced garlic cloves, and chiles de arbol and sautéed for a few minutes or until translucent on medium-low. Add paprika, tomato sauce, salt, and chili garlic sauce. Bring to a soft boil and remove from fire. Then blend up the sauce along with some veggie broth. 

Add the sauce to your slow cooker along with your potatoes (you can also sauté your potatoes before adding them). Cook on high for 3 hours. This will allow the potatoes to soak in all the flavor.  
Optional garnish with some vegan crema and scallions. My vegan crema was a mix of plant-based mayo with plant-based cream cheese and pickle juice. 
#CrockpotAmbassador #crockpotrecipes
➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖
Papas picantes 🌶 🔥
Para esta receta, usaré la olla de cocción lenta programable Choose-a-Crock de @crockpot

Ingredientes:
10-15 papas doradas pequeñas
1-2 tazas de salsa de tomate
1 taza de caldo de verduras
1/2 cebolla blanca
1 cucharada de paprika ahumado
2 dientes de ajo
5-8 chiles de árbol
Sal al gusto
1 cucharada de chili garlic (opcional)
En una sartén, agregue las cebollas picadas, los dientes de ajo picados y los chiles de árbol y saltee por unos minutos o hasta que estén transparentes (fuego medio-bajo). Agregue paprika, salsa de tomate, sal y salsa de ají con ajo. Llevar a ebullición y retirar del fuego. Luego licué la salsa junto con un poco de caldo de verduras.

Agregue la salsa a su olla de cocción lenta junto con sus papas (también puedes saltear sus papas antes de agregarlas). Cocine a fuego alto durante 3 horas. Esto permitirá que las papas absorban más sabor. 
Opcional: agrega con un poco de crema vegana y cebollín.

Today’s Chile Rellenos are sponsored by @LightlifeFoods #LightlifePartner Lightlife’s recently transformed portfolio brings plant-based enthusiasts so many vegan options to choose from! People who love or have been wanting to try plant-based protein can chose from more than 24 different options and flavors from Lightlife. 

Today, I chose to use their Smart Ground Plant-Based Crumbles. Lightlife’s Smart Ground Crumbles bring big flavor to the recipe, a perfect add for anyone interested in trying a plant-based twist on Chile Rellenos.

In a pan, sauté one big carrot, 1 bell pepper, 1 package of Smart Ground, 1/2 white onion, and season with salt and pepper to taste. 1 tsp cumin, 1 tsp garlic powder, 1 tsp paprika, and a dash of oregano. Cook until carrots are soft and tender. Optional add green peas at the end.
Cook the poblano peppers until the skin of the peppers have blackened and blistered. Turn the peppers often to blacken all sides. Once cool down, peel off the skins. Stuff the peppers with plant-based cheese and your Smart Ground stuffing. Put them back in the oven for a few minutes until the cheese melts and enjoy warm with a delicious sauce.

I made a chipotle mayo sauce by blending 1 chipotle in adobo sauce with silken tofu (1/2 block) or 1 cup of soaked cashews, add 1-2 garlic cloves, the juice of 1 lime, salt if needed, and water to desired consistency.

Enjoy your Chile Rellenos with beans and rice. And add as much sauce as you like. 😊 #Lightlife
➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖
Los Chile Rellenos de hoy son patrocinados por @LightlifeFoods #LightlifePartner Hoy, elegí usar sus Smart Ground Crumbles a base de plantas. 

En una sartén, saltee una zanahoria grande, 1 pimiento morrón, 1 paquete de Smart Ground, 1/2 cebolla blanca y sazone con sal y pimienta al gusto. 1 cucharadita de comino, 1 cucharadita de ajo en polvo, 1 cucharadita de pimentón y una pizca de orégano. Cocine hasta que las zanahorias estén suaves y tiernas. Opcional agregue chícharos al final. Dora los chiles poblanos hasta que la piel de los chiles se queme y se ampolle. Gire los pimientos con frecuencia. Una vez que se enfríen, retire la piel.

One of my favorite recipes
🥬King oyster mushroom “chicken” salad wrap!! 2 king oyster mushrooms shredded and sautéed until golden brown. Once sautéed, mix with fresh ingredients: celery, red onion, tomatoes, relish, and green onions. 

In a blender, add soaked cashews about 1 cup, one lemon, pepper, salt, dill weed, onion powder, 2 garlic cloves, and water to desired consistency. 

Add your sauce to your veggie mix (as much as you want 😉). Enjoy with lettuce or crackers 🙌🏻😋 #throwback

🥕 Carrot “rice” veggie rolls with baked tofu, marinated avocado, and veggies/fruits. First, I marinated my avocado with lime juice and tamari sauce. Then I shredded a few carrots and seasoned with garlic salt before squeezing the excess water. On a nori sheet, I spread my carrot rice, and added avocado, tofu, mango, and red bell peppers. Roll them up, cut, and decorated with spicy vegan mayo and serrano peppers. #throwbackthursday

🥕 Rollos con “arroz” de zanahoria, tofu al horno, aguacate marinado y verduras/frutas. Primero, mariné mi aguacate con jugo de limón y salsa tamari. Luego rallé las zanahorias y sazone con sal de ajo y exprimí el exceso de agua. En una hoja de nori, unte mi arroz de zanahoria y agregue aguacate, tofu, mango y pimientos rojos. Enrolle, corte y decore con mayonesa vegana picante y chiles serranos. 🥑

For this recipe, I’m using @lightlifefoods new and improved Smart Dogs! #LightlifePartner They recently refreshed their beloved hot dog along with several other products so that they’re made with more recognizable ingredients – love it!

Aligned, for this recipe you’ll want to cut a thin line down every smart dog and marinate them for at least 2 hours or overnight (You can skip this step, but I think it makes this recipe). The sauce consists of a mix of 1/2 cup rice vinegar, 1/2 cup tamari sauce, 1-2 tbsp sugar or agave, 1 tbsp hot sauce, and 1/2 tbsp garlic powder.
I also made a quick cilantro chimichurri by mixing a handful of cilantro, 3-4 scallions, 2 garlic cloves, 1/4 red onion, and 2-4 tbsp of olive oil, salt, and black pepper to taste and dash of oregano. Hop to it and pick up these Lightlife Smart Dogs at a H-E-B near you! Look for Lightlife at your local H-E-B. 
 
To make our pico de Gallo:
2 tomato tomatoes (no seeds)
1/2 white onion
1-2 tbsp pickled jalapeños
Salt to taste.

To make our mayo sauce:
2-3 tbsp of plant-based mayo
1 tbsp mustard
1/2 hot sauce

I grilled the Smart Dogs according to the directions on the package. Instead of regular hot dog buns, I'm doing toasted bolillos. Do your sauce first, then the grilled hot dogs, the pico de Gallo, caramelized onions (optional), cilantro chimichurri, and more hot sauce on top if you like. I know they are extra, but that flavor 🤤👨🏻‍🍳 #Lightlife
➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖
Para esta receta, estoy usando los nuevos y mejorados Smart Dogs de @lightlifefoods. Recientemente renovaron su amado hot dog junto con varios otros productos para que estén hechos con ingredientes más reconocibles. 

Para esta receta, corta una línea delgada en cada hot dog y marinarlos al menos 2 horas o durante la noche (puedes omitir este paso, pero creo que hace esta receta). La salsa consiste en una mezcla de 1/2 taza de vinagre de arroz, 1/2 taza salsa tamari, 1-2 cucharadas de azúcar o agave, 1 cucharada de salsa picante y 1/2 cucharada de ajo en polvo.

I can’t find a russet potato this big and not stuff it 😂. It took about 1hour 20 min at 430F to bake this baby. Optional while baking: cover in oil, salt, and garlic powder. 

While it was baking, I made tofu crumbles. 
I pressed extra-firm tofu with my hands, squeezing as much water as possible, then with your hands or a fork, break it apart. For seasonings, I did olive oil, oregano, cumin, garlic powder, soy sauce, A1 sauce or bbq, ketchup, and fajita seasoning. You want to season it pretty well. You can either air fry or bake it. I air-fried mine for 30 min at 400F shaking it every 10 min, so it cooks evenly. 

Once the potato is cooked, make a hole and remove as much potato as you want. In a bowl, mix the removed pota8 with unsweetened plant-based milk (start with small amounts) of your choice, vegan butter or oil to make the mix soft, add the crumbles, scallions and serve hot 😊 you can even add vegan cheese. Top it off with your favorite sauce.

Neto Craves 💚 
➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖
No puedo encontrar una papa tan grande y no rellenarla 😂. Tomó aproximadamente 1 hora y 20 minutos a 430F para hornear a este papota. Opcional: cubra con aceite, sal y ajo en polvo. 

Mientras se horneaba, hice una ‘carnita’ de tofu. Presioné el tofu extra firme con las manos, exprima la mayor cantidad de agua posible, luego, con las manos o un tenedor, quiébralo. Para los condimentos, utilicé aceite de oliva, orégano, comino, ajo en polvo, salsa de soja, salsa A1 o bbq, salsa de tomate y condimento para fajitas. Quieres sazonarlo bastante bien. Puedes freírlo al aire o hornearlo. Freí el mío al aire durante 30 minutos a 400F agitándolo cada 10 minutos, para que se cocine de manera uniforme. 

Una vez que la patata esté cocida, haz un hoyo y sácale papa 😉 . En un tazón, mezcle con leche vegetal sin azúcar (comience con pequeñas cantidades) de su elección, mantequilla vegana o aceite para ablandar la mezcla, agregue el tofu, las cebolletas y sirva caliente 😊 incluso puede agregar queso vegano 🧀

1 tomato

🍄Rice paper rolls with mushroom pulled “pork,” rice, and avocado. I’m using king oyster mushrooms. 

I marinated the mushrooms for about 30 min with a Korean bbq sauce (store-bought), tamari sauce, garlic and parsley powder, and some lime juice. Then you can sauté the mushrooms or baked them. I sautéed mine for 7-10 min. You want a darker color and smoky flavor cook for longer. 

Then in a burger bun or rice paper, add your rice, mushrooms, and avocado. Roll and enjoy with a sauce of your choice. I did a peanut butter sauce! 

Neto Craves 💚
➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖
🍄 Rollitos de papel de arroz con champiñones, arroz y aguacate. Yo use hongo ostra (king oyster). 

Mariné los champiñones durante unos 30 minutos con salsa bbq coreana (de tienda), salsa tamari, ajo y perejil en polvo y un poco de jugo de limon. Puedes saltear los champiñones o hornearlos. Yo los dore durante 7-10 min. Quieres un sabor ahumado y un color más oscuro dora por más tiempo. Luego, en un pan de hamburguesa o papel de arroz, agrega arroz, champiñones y aguacate. Enrolla y disfruta con una salsa de tu elección.

Today we are making flautas. #LightlifePartner This recipe is sponsored by @LightlifeFoods, and I will be using their Gimme Lean Sausage! This plant-based Sausage brings the mouth-watering sausage flavor but with 0mg of cholesterol. Enjoy sliced, diced or crumbled (for this recipe I crumbled). Be sure to check out other products from the new and improved Reformulated Product line.
First started by making our avocado Pico de Gallo:
2 roma tomatoes (no seeds)
1/2 avocado
2-4 scallions
1/2 red onion
1 jalapeño (no seeds)
Handful cilantro
1/2 lime juice
Salt to taste
Mix and store in the fridge while you make your flautas.

In a pan, add diced potatoes (I’m using half a big russet potato), 1/2 package of Lightlife Gimme Lean Sausage, a dash of cumin, garlic powder, and onion salt. Sautéed until golden brown and potatoes are soft and crunchy.
Once the stuffing is ready, warm up some tortillas, add the filling and roll them up. You can either fry them or back them until crunchy.
To make our avocado sauce:
Blend 1 big avocado, the juice of 1 lime, 2 raw tomatillos, 1/2 cup plant-based milk (unsweetened) if needed, salt and pepper to taste, 1 cup vegan sour cream or unsweetened plant-based yogurt. A handful of cilantro and 1 garlic clove.
Assemble your flautas add your sauce, lettuce, or cabbage, and top it off with avocado pico de Gallo. Enjoy them warm! #Lightlife

Creamy potato 🥔 salad. This recipe tastes better when it’s cold 🤤. In a pot, boil until soft potatoes of your choice. I did about 8-10 small golden potatoes. Once ready, set them aside for them to cool down. 

To make our sauce: 
Blend 1/2 block of silken tofu with a few tablespoons of vegetable broth until smooth. 

In a bowl, mix the tofu blend with 1-2 tbsp of sweet relish and 1-2 tbsp of pickled jalapeños. 2 tbsp of mustard, 1/2 tbsp garlic powder, 1/2 tbsp onion powder, and a dash of oregano. Adjust salt if needed. 

Add your sauce to the boiled potatoes along with fresh cucumbers, red onions, and scallions. 
Enjoy with crackers. 
➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖
Ensalada cremosa de pap. Esta receta sabe mejor cuando está fría 🤤. En una olla, hierve papas de tu elección hasta que estén suaves. Yo use de 8-10 papas doradas pequeñas. Una vez listas, déjalas a un lado para que se enfríen. 

Para hacer nuestra salsa: Licué 1/2 bloque de tofu de seda con unas cucharadas de caldo de verduras hasta que quede suave. 

En un tazón, mezcle el tofu con 1-2 cdas de pepinillos dulces y 1-2 cdas de jalapeños en escabeche, 2 cdas de mostaza, 1/2 cdta de ajo en polvo, 1/2 cdta de cebolla en polvo y una pizca de orégano. Ajuste la sal si es necesario. 

Agregue su salsa a las papas cocinadas junto con pepinos frescos, cebolla morada y cebollín. Disfruta de esta receta con galletas saladas. 

#veganrecipes #veganfood #vegano #mexicanvegan

Vegan “Shrimp” Cocktail. Ohh, 😍 this recipe I remember eating it all-time during the summer back in Mexico. It’s so fresh and easy to make. The key ingredients here are the heart of palms and seaweed (or dulse flakes). 

First, you want to start by chopping 1-2 cans of heart of palms, dash of salt, then add the juice of 3-4 limes and 1-2 toasted nori sheets or dulse flakes to give it that fishy 🐠 flavor. Let this marinate for 1-2 hours.  
In a bowl, mix 3 tomatoes, 2 small cucumbers, 1/4 red onion, 1 jalapeño, a handful of cilantro, the heart of palms, and salt to taste.  
Since the original recipe calls for Clamato, which is not vegan, I will be using 2 cups of vegetable juice and 2 cups of spicy vegetable juicy. (I found them at H-E-B). I’ll post them on my stories.  
Mix everything and store it in the fridge until it's cold. When it is ready to serve, add 1-2 avocados and enjoy with crackers or saltines. It's so yummy 🤤 

🕺🏻Ebook at netocraves.com (link in profile) ➖➖➖➖➖➖➖➖
Cóctel de “Camarones” Vegano. Oh, 😍 esta receta me encantaba comerla en el verano ☀️ en México. Es tan fresca y fácil de hacer. Los ingredientes clave aquí son los palmitos y las algas (o copos de dulse).

Primero, debes comenzar cortando 1-2 latas de palmitos, una pizca de sal, luego agrega el jugo de 3-4 limones y 1-2 hojas de nori tostadas o hojuelas para darle ese sabor a pescado. Deje marinar durante 1-2 horas.

En un bol, mezcla 3 tomates, 2 pepinos pequeños, 1/4 de cebolla morada, 1 jalapeño, un puño de cilantro, los palmitos y sal al gusto.

Dado que la receta original requiere Clamato, que no es vegano, usaré 2 tazas de jugo de vegetales y 2 tazas de jugo vegetal picante. (Los encontré en H-E-B). Los publicaré en mis historias.

Mezclar todo y guardar en el refrigerador hasta que esté frío. Cuando esté listo para servir, agrega 1-2 aguacates y disfrútalo con galletas saladas o tostadas. Es tan delicioso 🤤
